<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1328,1607]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1328,1354]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body moderately wide and elongate oval; elytra with more or less obliterate to obsolete striae; head sharply narrowed to base, with moderately small and finely faceted eyes located behind middle; prothoracic lateral carinae rather smoothed; pronotal anterior angles widely rounded; scutellar shield subpentangular; tibiae swollen (less dorsoventrally compressed) and with group of short and thick spines at apex; femora rather wide and thick; tarsi with moderately lobed tarsomeres 1–3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1328,1607]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,1508,1534]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Composition</emphasis>
. This subgenus includes one described species, although few undescribed species of it have been collected in New 
<collectingCountry box="[348,429,1544,1570]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and surrounding islands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
